<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[192,1440,1027,1115]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,328,1027,1051]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[342,429,1027,1051]" captionStart="Figure 47-58" captionStartId="13.[192,276,1825,1847]" captionTargetBox="[192,1443,192,1797]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[192,1443,192,1797]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figure 47-58. Habiti. 47) Amboakis ampla. 48) A. antegalba. 49) A. diffusa. 50) Amboakis demagna. 51) A. waodani. 52) Epiphloeus erwini. 53) Madoniella aspera. 54) Madoniella darlingtoni. 55). Madoniella divida. 56) Madoniella spilota. 57) Plocamocera clinata. 58) P. lena." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5352840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5352840/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
): In the key of madoniellan species (Opitz, in press), the 
<typeStatus box="[1105,1216,1027,1051]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Holotype</typeStatus>
extends to couplet 11(4'), which accommodates 
<taxonomicName authority="Opitz. From" authorityName="Opitz. From" box="[547,939,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Madoniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubida">
<emphasis box="[547,780,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Madoniella rubida</emphasis>
Opitz. From
</taxonomicName>
the latter, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2010" box="[1082,1207,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Madoniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spilota">
<emphasis box="[1082,1107,1060,1083]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1123,1207,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">spilota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens may be distinguished by the spotted condition of the legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[192,1441,1155,1371]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,364,1155,1179]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[375,426,1156,1179]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Size</emphasis>
: Length 
<quantity box="[535,629,1155,1179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity box="[716,810,1155,1179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[820,1058,1155,1179]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Integumental Color</emphasis>
: Cranium dark reddish-brown; pronotal disc dark brown, more reddish at sides; elytral disc with well-developed insignia, posterolateral extensions of posterior block missing, posterocentral extension of posterior block broadly confluent with yellow macula on elytral apex. 
<emphasis box="[557,622,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Head</emphasis>
: Vertex narrower than eyes in head dorsal view; antenna as depicted in figure 11. 
<emphasis box="[348,437,1283,1307]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotal side margins very sinuous, anterior margin arcuate plane; elytral form oblong; elytral punctations large; anterior margin of protibia with 5 spines. 
<emphasis box="[1140,1256,1315,1339]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Aedeagus not available for study.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[192,648,1411,1435]" box="[192,648,1411,1435]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,333,1411,1435]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Variation.</emphasis>
One specimen examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[192,1440,1473,1531]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,419,1475,1499]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">Natural History.</emphasis>
The primary 
<typeStatus box="[591,645,1476,1500]" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
was collected at 
<quantity box="[849,939,1475,1499]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="17" pageNumber="16" unit="m" value="1850.0">1850 m</quantity>
sometime between October 29 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1311,1326,1473,1487]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">th</superScript>
and September 18 
<superScript attach="none" box="[315,330,1505,1519]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="16">th</superScript>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
